habitat_description: Callorhinus ursinus has only two known breeding sites in the conterminous U.S.: San Miguel Island, CA (Antonelis and Fiscus, 1980; DeLong and Melin, 2000; Burton et al., 2001) and the Farallon Islands (Burton et al., 2001). During the breeding season, the species uses both rocky and sandy beaches (NOAA, 2014). The remainder of the year, the species remains far offshore, typically between 74 and 130 km from land (Kajimura, 1980; Antonelis and Perez, 1984).
